In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks; beat well. Blend in milk. Stir in nuts and raisins; set aside. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into the raisin mixture. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees F for 15 minutes. Reduce the temperature to 300 degrees F; bake 40 minutes longer or until lightly browned. Cool. Refrigerate. Serve pie chilled with whipped cream if desired.